{
  "stem": "4284.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I worked 12 to 14 hours or more sometimes in an agricultural manner in plowing fields and planting for vegetables, with an additional bonus of being able at harvest time to steal food.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "At one time I hid a lot of carrots, and my mother and I would share it with the people in the room, which was a rarity, believe me, that you even had enough to share.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we ate so many carrots, including at work, that I promptly turned yellow and had jaundice from basically, a vitamin-- as we now know, a vitamin A toxic level.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I looked like a pretty sick individual, which was a very dangerous thing to be, because when Germans inspected you and you didn't look healthy, you had no guarantee of being around the next day because various types of selection took place.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Except it wasn't organized selection.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I was there from 1941 to 1943.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Managed to get by, scrounging, stealing, eating anything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "We discovered, for example, that when I had to work on the fields, that there was a peculiar plant that was edible.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And you kept it as an absolute secret that you could eat  that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "You ate everything and anything you could find.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I only it as [POLISH], which is the Polish name.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The one that I do remember, which was an absolute treat, was dandelion.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It became a regular science because you ate the dandelion only before it bloomed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Otherwise, it became inedible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You just could not eat the incredible bitterness.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so you looked around and you waited for a little dandelion.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The joke was also that because I worked in the agricultural capacity that I had a tiny, tiny plot of land where I could do something for myself.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
